### Affected Package
"@angular/compiler": "10.1.3",
"@angular/core": "10.1.3",


### Is this a regression?

Did this behavior use to work in the previous version? 
Yes, the previous version in which this bug was not present was: 9


### Description

I have an Angular Library that contains my shared components in a component module. when I build my library with 
`ng build lcf --prod`
everything works fine and builds without any err.
but when I start serve my app which I import and use mt lib everything fails and throw this err :

`class VideoPlayerComponent {
               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    dist/lcf/__ivy_ngcc__/fesm2015/lcf.js:3410:7 - error NG2007: Class is using Angular features but is not decorated. Please add an explicit Angular decorator.
`
I did not get the err before but I don't know what happened suddenly to my lib.

## my component on lib 
<pre><code>
